ught.\r\n<h4>Thursday - Beginners</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nDynamic class suitable for those with little or no experience in yoga. All basic yoga postures will be taught including shoulder stand and relaxation.\r\n<h4>Friday - Restorative</h4>\r\n<em>1 - 2pm</em>\r\nThis is a slower pace class suitable for all levels. Poses will be practised supported to help the body recover at the end of the week. This type of practice helps us prolong the timing in the poses and deepen the experience. More attention is given to the breath and basic breathing exercises will be taught regularly in this class.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;">Classes are suitable for all, no previous yoga experience needed!</span>\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 24px;">Prices from January</span></h1>\r\n<h4>1 hour Lunchtime Class</h4>\r\n<h1><span style="font-size: 24px;"><img class="alignright  wp-image-172" style="margin: 10px;" title="£49 for 10 classes" alt="£49 for 10 Classes" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/49for10circle-300x300.png" width="180" height="180" /></span></h1>\r\n<span style="color: #ff0000;"><em>*New Student Offer!</em></span>\r\n10-class Yogacard - £49 for 6 weeks\r\n\r\n10-class Yogacard - £70 for 12 weeks\r\n\r\nDrop-in - £8\r\n<h4>1.5 hour Evening classes</h4>\r\n10-class Yogacard - £90 for 12 weeks\r\nDrop-in - £10\r\n\r\n<a title="Coming Soon!">View full Yoga Loft Timetable here!</a>\r\n\r\nYogaloft is a fully equipped studio at Queen Square, Bristol\r\n\r\n<img class=" wp-image-181 alignleft" style="margin-right: 20px; margin-left: 20px;" title="Osteopaths" alt="Osteopaths Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/Osteopaths-Logo.png" width="38" height="24" />Osteopaths, 57 Queen Charlotte Street, Bristol BS1 4HQ\r\n<iframe src="https://maps.google.co.uk/maps?ie=UTF8&amp;cid=3098133523227739122&amp;gl=GB&amp;hl=en&amp;t=m&amp;ll=51.451533,-2.594211&amp;spn=0.05,0.05&amp;z=16&amp;&amp;iwloc=near&amp;output=embed" height="350" width="600" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>', '', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '154-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-02 18:23:47', '2013-12-02 18:23:47', '', 154, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/154-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wpydnv_posts` VALUES (214, 1, '2013-12-02 18:29:19', '2013-12-02 18:29:19', '<h2>Andrea Ray</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-151" style="margin-left: 25px; margin-right: 25px;" title="Andrea Ray" alt="Andrea profile" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Andrea-profileshoot-640-300x200.jpg" width="300" height="200" />I was introduced to Iyengar Yoga at an early age, about 20 years ago. I have come a long way since and have now been teaching many public classes for the past 8 years. I hold Junior Intermediate Teaching Level 3 qualification.\r\n\r\nMore than just the physical postures, yoga as a philosophy has always fascinated me. I feel very fortunate to have access to the never-ageing wisdom through the work of Patanjali’s Yogasutras and through more recent works of BKS Iyengar that has brought Yoga to the world’s consciousness.\r\n\r\nMy daily practice is focused on finding deeper connection with myself and reconnecting with the core of being. I’ve been fortunate to study under many wise and knowledgeable teachers from all around the world as well as with the Iyengar family.\r\n\r\nTeaching is a great joy. I enjoy teaching students new to yoga and seeing the positive changes it brings. I also enjoy working with experienced students a on much more subtle level to help them find the teacher within them. Dealing with my own obstacles on the path has made me more compassionate and understanding.\r\n\r\nIyengar yoga offers endless variety of approaches and I focus on using the appropriate tools according to the need of students, and the cycle of nature.\r\n\r\nI currently practice, live and teach in Bristol.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;"><span style="line-height: 1.5;">You can also </span><a style="line-height: 1.5;" title="My Iyengar Yoga Profile" href="https://www.iyengaryoga.org.uk/profile/4796" target="_blank">visit my Profile</a><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> on the Iyengar Yoga Association UK website.</span></span>', 'About Me', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-12-02 18:29:19', '2013-12-02 18:29:19', '', 4, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
