INSERT INTO `wpydnv_posts` VALUES (371, 1, '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '<h3><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-250" style="margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" alt="BCY-Logo" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/BCY-Logo.jpg" width="124" height="85" />6 week Pranayama Course</h3>\r\n<address>Wednesdays 6 - 7.15pm</address> <strong>22nd January - 26th February 2014</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bristol City Yoga</strong>\r\n<a href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk">www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk </a>\r\n<em>16 Backfields Lane, Bristol, BS2 8QW</em>\r\n\r\nThis course will be introducing basic breath control techniques.\r\nPranayama is a more subtle part of yoga practice, where one conditions the flow of breath by changing its the length and pace, and by introducing new patterns. Although classically practiced in seated posture, we will first introduce it in supine poses.\r\n\r\nThe breath is a gateway to the inside world. With awareness of breath, our consciousness spreads to more subtle parts of the body. This is not possible by focusing only on the physical body, as it initially happens in our asana practice.\r\n\r\nBy freeing the breath with correct positioning of the body and introduction of various breathing techniques, the inner balance and energy is restored, hence the name Pranayama, which refers to the life energy of the body.\r\n\r\nPractice of Pranayama is a great practice of mindfulness, as the mind is focused within on the flow and pattern of the breath. This gives us a sense of stillness and serenity.\r\n\r\nThis course is meant for students who have been practicing yoga for some time and would like to deepen their practice by learning more about the breath. Previous Pranayama knowledge is not required.\r\n\r\n£50 for the course\r\n<a title="Bristol City Yoga Pranayama Course" href="http://www.bristolcityyoga.co.uk/classes-and-courses/courses/pranayama-course/" target="_blank">Book your Pranayama course online</a>\r\nOr contact BCY:\r\nphone: 0117 924 4414\r\ne-mail: info@bristolcityyoga.co.uk', 'Yoga Day ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '220-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '2014-03-18 14:17:46', '', 220, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/220-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
