INSERT INTO `wpydnv_posts` VALUES (395, 1, '2014-05-26 12:29:18', '2014-05-26 12:29:18', '<h2>Andrea Ray</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-151" style="margin-left: 25px; margin-right: 25px;" title="Andrea Ray" alt="Andrea profile" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/Andrea-profileshoot-640-300x200.jpg" width="300" height="200" />I was introduced to Iyengar Yoga at an early age, about 20 years ago. I have come a long way since and have now been teaching many public classes for the past 8 years. I hold Junior Intermediate Teaching Level 3 qualification.\r\n\r\nMore than just the physical postures, yoga as a philosophy has always fascinated me. I feel very fortunate to have access to the never-ageing wisdom through the work of Patanjali’s Yogasutras and through more recent works of BKS Iyengar that has brought Yoga to the world’s consciousness.\r\n\r\nMy daily practice is focused on finding deeper connection with myself and reconnecting with the core of being. I’ve been fortunate to study under many wise and knowledgeable teachers from all around the world as well as with the Iyengar family.\r\n\r\nTeaching is a great joy. I enjoy teaching students new to yoga and seeing the positive changes it brings. I also enjoy working with experienced students a on much more subtle level to help them find the teacher within them. Dealing with my own obstacles on the path has made me more compassionate and understanding.\r\n\r\nIyengar yoga offers endless variety of approaches and I focus on using the appropriate tools according to the need of students, and the cycle of nature.\r\n\r\nI\'ve recently moved back to London and I\'m currently on maternity leave. I\'ll be looking to teach again in early 2015 around West London. In the recent past, I\'ve been teaching in Bristol and around Central and North London.\r\n\r\n<span style="line-height: 1.5;"><span style="line-height: 1.5;">You can also </span><a style="line-height: 1.5;" title="My Iyengar Yoga Profile" href="https://www.iyengaryoga.org.uk/profile/4796" target="_blank">visit my Profile</a><span style="line-height: 1.5;"> on the Iyengar Yoga Association UK website.</span></span>', 'About Me', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-26 12:29:18', '2014-05-26 12:29:18', '', 4, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT INTO `wpydnv_posts` VALUES (396, 1, '2014-05-26 13:19:04', '2014-05-26 13:19:04', '<h4><img alt="Stick figure Yoga" src="http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/shapeimage_41.png" width="910" height="492" /></h4>\r\nI\'ve recently moved from Bristol to West London and I\'m currently on maternity leave. I\'ll be looking to start teaching classes again in early 2015.\r\n\r\nI teach wide range of  General public classes at yoga studios, Private classes and Corporate classes. Please contact me if you are interested to arrange a class to suite your needs.\r\n<h3>Private classes</h3>\r\nMostly one to one classes with the benefit of focusing directly on your specific needs and goals. Great way to get to know and understand your body whilst addressing particular tendencies specific to your structure and current state. Teaching one to one is a traditional way of teaching which allows the student to practice exactly according to personal needs under close guidance of experienced teacher.\r\n\r\nFamily class or a class of small group of friends could also be arranged.\r\n\r\nThese classes are offered at the comfort of your own home and you will have to provide the required equipment.\r\n\r\nPrice per 1 hour class is £60  and I currently teach in West and Central London.\r\n<h3>Corporate Classes</h3>\r\nArranging a yoga class for your employes is a fantastic way to improve the work moral and health of your workers. Yoga helps build up strength, stamina, balance and flexibility, whilst creating balanced mental state with strong sense of vitality and health.\r\n\r\nI offer lunchtime and evening classes at the comfort of your office. You\'ll have to provide a suitable space to accommodate all the participants. Basic yoga equipment will also have to be provided by the office or the participants.\r\n\r\nPrice for 1 hour class is £75.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&lt;!--[subpage_peek]&gt;', 'Classes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '37-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-05-26 13:19:04', '2014-05-26 13:19:04', '', 37, 'http://localhost:8888/wpyogdiksha-nov2013/posts/37-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
